{"word":"χρυσίον","slug":"χρυσίον","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>χρυσίον</b></el> <el>(χρῡσίον, ου, τό,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:Diminutive'>Dim.</a> of <el>χρύσος</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a piece of gold</i>, generally, <i>gold</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>gold coin, money</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>χρυσία</el> <i>pieces of gold</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as a term of endearment, <i>my golden one! my little treasure!</i> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}